  "description": "¶Entry conditions Use homotopy only when you have topological spaces and continuous maps between them.\n¶Definitions Two continuous maps f,g:X→Yf,g:X \\to Y are homotopic if there exists a continuous map H:X×[0,1]→Y H:X \\times [0,1] \\to Y with H(x,0)=f(x)H(x,0)=f(x) and H(x,1)=g(x)H(x,1)=g(x).\n¶Vocabulary (plain language) Deformation: a continuous transformation over time. Parameter: the time variable in [0,1][0,1]. ¶Symbols used HH: the homotopy between ff and gg. ¶Intuition Homotopy says that two maps are the same if one can be continuously deformed into the other.\n",
